- **Fake Testing Requirements:**
  - **Create `.test.ts` file** for each fake implementation
  - **Test fake behavior** matches expected interface contracts
  - **Verify call tracking** works correctly
  - **Test reset functionality** clears all state
  - **Test helper methods** for adding test data

- **Error Simulation:**
  - **Use boolean flags and error fields** per method for error simulation
  - **Pattern**: `methodNameShouldThrow: boolean` and `methodNameError: Error | null`
  - **Check flags in method implementation** before processing
  - **Reset error flags** in `reset()` method for test isolation
  - **Example:**
  ```typescript
  // ✅ DO: Per-method error simulation flags
  export class RepositoryFake {
    public createShouldThrow = false;
    public createError: Error | null = null;
    
    async create(...args): Promise<Entity> {
      this.createCallArgs.push(...args);
      
      if (this.createShouldThrow) {
        const error = this.createError ?? new Error('Create failed');
        return Promise.reject(error);
      }
      
      // Normal implementation
    }
    
    reset(): void {
      this.createShouldThrow = false;
      this.createError = null;
    }
  }
  
  // ✅ DO: Use flags in tests instead of method overrides
  it('should handle create errors', async () => {
    repositoryFake.createShouldThrow = true;
    repositoryFake.createError = new Error('Database error');
    // Test error handling
  });
  
  // ❌ DON'T: Override methods in tests
  repositoryFake.create = async () => {
    repositoryFake.createCallArgs.push(...);
    throw new Error('Database error');
  };
  ```

- **Performance Considerations:**
  - **Keep fakes lightweight** - avoid complex business logic
  - **Use in-memory storage** for test data
  - **Implement only necessary methods** for current test needs
  - **Avoid external dependencies** in fake implementations

- **Documentation Standards:**
  - **Document fake purpose** and which real service it replaces
  - **Explain test data setup** methods and their usage
  - **Note limitations** of the fake implementation
  - **Provide usage examples** in JSDoc comments

